<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>FxCop on Code it Yourself...</title><link>https://carlos.mendible.com/tags/fxcop/</link><description>Recent content in FxCop on Code it Yourself...</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><copyright>Copyright &amp;copy; 2020 - Carlos Mendible</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 05 Apr 2018 07:21:39 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://carlos.mendible.com/tags/fxcop/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Adding Code Analysis and StyleCop checks to .NET Core projects with dotnet-addcasa</title><link>https://carlos.mendible.com/2018/04/05/adding-code-analysis-and-stylecop-checks-to-net-core-projects-with-dotnet-addcasa/</link><pubDate>Thu, 05 Apr 2018 07:21:39 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://carlos.mendible.com/2018/04/05/adding-code-analysis-and-stylecop-checks-to-net-core-projects-with-dotnet-addcasa/</guid><description>&lt;p>Today I&amp;rsquo;ll show you how to use &lt;a href="https://github.com/cmendible/dotnet-addcasa">dotnet-addcasa&lt;/a>: a .NET Core global tool to add CodeAnalysis and Stylecop checks to your projects.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>If you want to manually add those checks or understand the tool internals check my post: &lt;a href="https://carlos.mendible.com/2017/08/24/dotnet-core-code-analysis-and-stylecop/">.NET Core, Code Analysis and StyleCop&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="1-prerequisites">1. Prerequisites&lt;/h2>
&lt;hr>
&lt;p>You&amp;rsquo;ll need &lt;a href="https://www.microsoft.com/net/download/dotnet-core/sdk-2.1.300-preview1">.NET Core SDK 2.1.300-preview1&lt;/a> installed.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="2-install-the-dotnet-addcasa-net-core-tool">2. Install the dotnet-addcasa .NET Core tool&lt;/h2>
&lt;hr>
&lt;p>To install &lt;a href="https://github.com/cmendible/dotnet-addcasa">dotnet-addcasa&lt;/a> as a global tool run:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4">&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell">dotnet tool install -g dotnet-addcasa
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="3-add-code-analysis-and-stylecop-checks-to-your-projects">3. Add Code Analysis and StyleCop checks to your projects&lt;/h2>
&lt;hr>
&lt;p>To add CodeAnalysis and StyleCop to all your projects run the following command from the root folder of your solution or workspace.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4">&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell">dotnet addcasa
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>The tool is a work in progress so feel free to contribute &lt;a href="https://github.com/cmendible/dotnet-addcasa">here&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Hope it helps!&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>.NET Core, Code Analysis and StyleCop</title><link>https://carlos.mendible.com/2017/08/24/dotnet-core-code-analysis-and-stylecop/</link><pubDate>Thu, 24 Aug 2017 17:01:39 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://carlos.mendible.com/2017/08/24/dotnet-core-code-analysis-and-stylecop/</guid><description>&lt;p>So now that .NET Core and .NET Standard 2.0 have been released some of you may be migrating applications or even creating new ones with it. As you progress you are starting to worry about the quality of your code so what you want is to at least check your code against design and style guidelines don&amp;rsquo;t you?&lt;/p>
&lt;p>This post will show you how easy is to make &lt;strong>.NET Core, Code Analysis and StyleCop&lt;/strong> play along together.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Here you go:&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="1-create-a-folder-for-your-new-project">1. Create a folder for your new project&lt;/h2>
&lt;hr>
&lt;p>Open a command prompt an run:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4">&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell">mkdir codeanalysis
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="2-create-the-project">2. Create the project&lt;/h2>
&lt;hr>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4">&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell">cd codeanalysis
dotnet new console
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="3-add-the-references-for-codeanalysis-and-stylecop">3. Add the references for CodeAnalysis and StyleCop&lt;/h2>
&lt;hr>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4">&lt;code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell">dotnet add package Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.FxCopAnalyzers
dotnet add package StyleCop.Analyzers
dotnet restore
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="4-add-codeanalysisruleset-property-to-the-project">4. Add CodeAnalysisRuleSet property to the project&lt;/h2>
&lt;hr>
&lt;p>Open the file &lt;strong>codeanalysis.csproj&lt;/strong> and add the following property inside a Property Group:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4">&lt;code class="language-xml" data-lang="xml">&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;CodeAnalysisRuleSet&amp;gt;&lt;/span>ca.ruleset&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;/CodeAnalysisRuleSet&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>or add a new Property Group:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4">&lt;code class="language-xml" data-lang="xml">&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;PropertyGroup&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;CodeAnalysisRuleSet&amp;gt;&lt;/span>ca.ruleset&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;/CodeAnalysisRuleSet&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;/PropertyGroup&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="5-create-the-caruleset-file">5. Create the ca.ruleset file&lt;/h2>
&lt;hr>
&lt;p>Create a ca.ruleset file and replace it&amp;rsquo;s content with the following xml:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4">&lt;code class="language-xml" data-lang="xml">&lt;span style="color:#75715e">&amp;lt;?xml version=&amp;#34;1.0&amp;#34; encoding=&amp;#34;utf-8&amp;#34;?&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;RuleSet&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Name=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Custom Rulset&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Description=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Custom Rulset&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">ToolsVersion=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;14.0&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;Rules&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">AnalyzerId=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;AsyncUsageAnalyzers&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">RuleNamespace=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;AsyncUsageAnalyzers&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;Rule&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Id=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;UseConfigureAwait&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Action=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Warning&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">/&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;/Rules&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;Rules&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">AnalyzerId=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Microsoft.Analyzers.ManagedCodeAnalysis&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">RuleNamespace=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Microsoft.Rules.Managed&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;Rule&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Id=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;CA1001&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Action=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Warning&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">/&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;Rule&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Id=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;CA1009&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Action=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Warning&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">/&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;Rule&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Id=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;CA1016&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Action=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Warning&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">/&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;Rule&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Id=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;CA1033&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Action=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Warning&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">/&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;Rule&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Id=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;CA1049&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Action=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Warning&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">/&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
&lt;span style="color:#f92672">&amp;lt;Rule&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Id=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;CA1060&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e">Action=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;Warning&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f92672">/&amp;gt;&lt;/span>
